profile_positions.description:
- Transport Coordination (transport planning and follow up) and Quality Control; 
- Development and improvement of standard operations procedures and quality processes; 
- Assistance in implementation of project software;
- Synchronization of the planning processes for the different EU et non-EU suppliers;
- Resolution of logistics issues and customs problems;
- Interaction with customers/ suppliers/ carriers;
- Continuous monitoring of carriers’ performance by KPIs implementation;
- Claims’ control – development of claims procedures and improvement of claims software;
- Registration of litigations/claims, conduct of investigation with the aim to find the damage responsible entity, control of claims’ payment).

Key achievements:
Successful launching of new projects related to the optimization of customers’ supply chains – project structure design; development of standard operations procedures and quality processes; setting KPIs to measure the projects’ progress.

-	Conduct of environmental inspections of Bulgarian and foreign flagged ships for compliance with international and European legislation; 
-	Sampling of marine fuels used by ships calling at or operating in the Bulgarian response area;
-	Exchange of information with the EU States’ control authorities regarding ships’ inspections; 
-	Regular monitoring (visual and satellite) of the marine environment in the Bulgarian response area;
-	Investigation and evidence gathering in case of ship-sourced pollution (oil spill modeling and monitoring; oil spill sampling and investigation; oil spill response activities); 
-	Contingency planning (Black Sea and Bulgarian National Oil Spill Contingency Plans); 
-	Drawing up proposals for adoption of and amendments to national legislation, related to protection of the marine environment;
-	Participation in international projects on maritime safety and pollution issues;
-	Periodical submission of statistical information to national/ international entities (e.g. BGR Ministry of Environment and Water, European Maritime Safety Agency, International Maritime Organisation (IMO)); 
-	Provision of protocol support for national and international meetings and events (workshops, visits, conferences and seminars);
-	Carrying out internal audits of BMA Quality control system.

Key achievements:
- Project Assistant in marine environment protection field (e.g. Ship Waste Management Information Database Setup; Vessel Traffic Oil Pollution Information System Development to support Governmental bodies in oil pollution management; Proposals for improvement of the European Thetis-S and Thetis-PRF systems ensuring harmonized approach for the inspection of ships for compliance with EU Sulphur and Port Reception Facilities Directives);

- Contribution to implementation of EU and international maritime legislation into the national legislation;

- Provision of successful oil-spill response activities and investigation in case of ship-sourced pollution.

- Organisation of courses under the auspices of IMO, as well as national and international events; 
- Participation in examination sessions for acquiring seafarer competency;
- Translation and interpretation of documents in the maritime transport field.

Key achievements:
Delivery of various national and international meetings and events (IMO courses, conferences, workshops, seminars, international exercises, etc.)

-	Keeping the agenda of the Managing Director up-to-date (appointments, meetings, etc.); 
-	Maintaining filing system, taking care of business correspondence;
-	Arranging all travel formalities for the Managing Director;
-	Translation of documents, drafting, proof reading of reports, minutes of meetings, etc.;
-	Assistance in preparation of marketing contracts;
-	Preparation of offers for tourist services provision; 
-	Negotiations with clients and businesses; 
-	Assistance in development of budget support plans for different events;
-	Creation and development of medium to large scale events like business conferences, seminars, workshops, official ceremonies, fairs, exhibitions, etc. (administrative and coordinating activities); 
- Preparation of economic analyses and prognoses with regard to tourist activity results;
- Conduct and analysis of inquiries among customers, summarizing the information and drafting reports.

Key achievements:
Assistance in the development of marketing, advertising, media and public relations strategy and tactics; identification of tourist demands; tourist market research.

- Translation of ship-related and other technical documentation;
- Interpretation during negotiations with potential customers;
- Support to the Trade Department (assistance in preparing offers, executing ship spare parts purchase orders, dealing with shipping documents, etc.).
Key achievements:
- Facilitation of the contract agreements with clients and suppliers.
